00:32:01.168 --> 00:32:04.528
all the pathogenic variants identified on those

556
00:32:05.028 --> 00:32:08.348
cancer genes. There's a panel, and they did a whole genome sequencing.

557
00:32:09.108 --> 00:32:12.668
And then they provide confirmative testing free of

558
00:32:12.748 --> 00:32:16.708
charge, and also provide genetic counseling, just like James

559
00:32:16.748 --> 00:32:17.048
said.

560
00:32:18.508 --> 00:32:20.708
So I think people benefit from this.

561
00:32:20.788 --> 00:32:23.948
Oh, they also return pharmacogenomic data.

562
00:32:24.548 --> 00:32:28.348
Some of these actionable interaction with drugs, so it's

