00:32:28.388 --> 00:32:29.208
good for them to know.

564
00:32:31.388 --> 00:32:35.208
That's great. Sounds like a lot more work needs to happen to be able to do

565
00:32:35.288 --> 00:32:38.898
this and meet the needs of the community as well as what we can fund in

566
00:32:38.928 --> 00:32:41.408
the extramural cohorts. So thank you.

567
00:32:42.248 --> 00:32:45.488
I want to move on now to thinking about recruitment and retention.

568
00:32:45.548 --> 00:32:49.388
We do have some new cohorts that are doing recruitment using

569
00:32:49.398 --> 00:32:52.968
novel ways, and I really want to hear from Wei and

570
00:32:53.008 --> 00:32:56.408
Iona on lessons learned that have emerged

571
00:32:56.888 --> 00:33:00.468
during recruitment and retention of our newly funded cohorts that are

572
00:33:00.508 --> 00:33:04.208
particularly relevant for thinking about the future cohorts that we

573
00:33:04.267 --> 00:33:07.128
might need to be planned.

574
00:33:08.788 --> 00:33:09.968
Go ahead.

575
00:33:10.788 --> 00:33:14.728
So the biggest lesson we learned is that response rate is much lower

576
00:33:15.148 --> 00:33:18.908
than it used to be . So we need to work really hard

577
00:33:19.128 --> 00:33:21.628
to really improve the response rate.

578
00:33:22.488 --> 00:33:25.328
There's certain many things we can do,

579
00:33:26.188 --> 00:33:28.328
but I just want to highlight two things.

580
00:33:28.568 --> 00:33:30.788
I think Iona can add some other things.

581
00:33:31.468 --> 00:33:32.708
One is the building trust.

582
00:33:33.548 --> 00:33:33.828
So

583
00:33:34.868 --> 00:33:35.968
some of you know that

584
00:33:36.948 --> 00:33:40.928
about 20 years ago, we started a study called Southern Community

585
00:33:41.028 --> 00:33:45.008
Cohort Study. The study led initially by Bill

586
00:33:45.028 --> 00:33:45.428
Broad.

587
00:33:46.668 --> 00:33:49.468
So the major aim for that study is to

588
00:33:50.268 --> 00:33:53.668
recruit African American and low-income American.

589
00:33:54.428 --> 00:33:55.908
So those people are really

590
00:33:56.728 --> 00:34:00.688
underrepresented in large cohort study.

591
00:34:01.688 --> 00:34:02.588
So to do that,

592
00:34:03.568 --> 00:34:07.308
Bill Broad developed a novel strategy

593
00:34:07.628 --> 00:34:10.548
to recruit people from the community health center.

594
00:34:11.268 --> 00:34:15.028
So as you know these centers provide affordable care,

595
00:34:15.188 --> 00:34:16.388
even just free care

596
00:34:17.248 --> 00:34:19.008
to underserved population.

597
00:34:19.928 --> 00:34:23.748
As this result, we actually in partnership with 71

598
00:34:24.208 --> 00:34:27.188
community health center across 12 southern states

599
00:34:28.089 --> 00:34:31.408
we recruited about 70,000 study

600
00:34:31.448 --> 00:34:33.368
participants through this

601
00:34:34.928 --> 00:34:36.928
network. So this lesson is still

602
00:34:37.948 --> 00:34:41.868
applicable to our new study we call Southern Environmental Health

603
00:34:41.968 --> 00:34:42.988
Study. We started in

604
00:34:43.788 --> 00:34:46.129
2021 to recruit

605
00:34:46.728 --> 00:34:50.708
35,000 people, and we particularly want to recruit

606
00:34:51.149 --> 00:34:54.609
low-income population because they tend to live

607
00:34:54.688 --> 00:34:58.608
in no economic resource area and

608
00:34:58.648 --> 00:34:58.908
also

609
00:34:59.948 --> 00:35:03.508
environment polluted area. So we use this approach

610
00:35:04.228 --> 00:35:07.448
so the community health center not only help us recruit

611
00:35:07.468 --> 00:35:11.288
participants, but also help us refine study

612
00:35:11.628 --> 00:35:12.988
protocols and the questionnaire.

613
00:35:13.708 --> 00:35:17.048
So I think one thing we learn from that is build trust.

614
00:35:17.708 --> 00:35:20.908
Another one is using the new

615
00:35:20.948 --> 00:35:21.708
technologies.

616
00:35:22.648 --> 00:35:26.588
So in the past, we typically used a paper form of consent,

617
00:35:26.728 --> 00:35:30.568
like paper questionnaire, those kind of things, doing phone

618
00:35:30.588 --> 00:35:31.148
interview,

619
00:35:32.068 --> 00:35:33.048
in-person interview.

620
00:35:34.528 --> 00:35:38.038
But that technology has really evolved for

621
00:35:38.348 --> 00:35:42.288
many years now. So for the new study, we

622
00:35:42.328 --> 00:35:45.628
call SEHS, we develop IT system.

623
00:35:46.468 --> 00:35:50.128
So we do this digital recruitment and also e-consent.

624
00:35:50.808 --> 00:35:51.848
Probably not new for

625
00:35:53.128 --> 00:35:56.718
many of you, but that work well, particularly when you have

626
00:35:57.328 --> 00:35:58.928
a limited resource.

627
00:36:00.548 --> 00:36:04.048
Participants can complete the online survey, but

628
00:36:04.088 --> 00:36:08.068
certainly there are some problem that we probably, if I have time, so we can

629
00:36:08.128 --> 00:36:08.828
go there.

630
00:36:10.188 --> 00:36:13.788
And also we use social

631
00:36:13.828 --> 00:36:17.208
medias like Facebook, Instagram to

632
00:36:17.788 --> 00:36:19.468
reach a large area.

633
00:36:20.348 --> 00:36:24.268
This is particularly important because the environment health study, we

634
00:36:24.308 --> 00:36:27.288
want to cover a large area of the population.

635
00:36:28.108 --> 00:36:32.028
So we end up actually recruit people from the 17 southern

636
00:36:32.108 --> 00:36:35.948
state and also DC area. So I think that's

637
00:36:36.128 --> 00:36:37.348
one thing, technology.

638
00:36:38.148 --> 00:36:41.568
Another thing we are doing is using wearable device.

639
00:36:42.008 --> 00:36:44.268
We use the silicon wristband

640
00:36:45.128 --> 00:36:48.528
to collect the external exposure sample

641
00:36:49.328 --> 00:36:53.128
that we can analyze about 500 chemical signatures.

642
00:36:54.068 --> 00:36:57.448
So a lot of participants are fascinated with this

643
00:36:57.508 --> 00:37:00.908
technology, so they are willing to participate.

644
00:37:00.968 --> 00:37:01.928
It's a high-tech study,

645
00:37:02.928 --> 00:37:04.488
kind of attractive. And also in

646
00:37:05.288 --> 00:37:06.888
the past, when you want to do these

647
00:37:08.268 --> 00:37:08.948
air pollution

648
00:37:09.636 --> 00:37:11.736
collection, you use pump. This is pretty heavy.

649
00:37:12.156 --> 00:37:15.896
The wristband is small, so I think the burden to

650
00:37:15.936 --> 00:37:19.396
participant is low, so they are more willing to do that.

651
00:37:19.616 --> 00:37:23.396
Certainly, some people concerned about when the drug they use can

652
00:37:23.976 --> 00:37:27.836
get into the wristband we analyze, so that's another story.

653
00:37:28.256 --> 00:37:30.756
But a lot of things we can do. AI, maybe.

654
00:37:30.986 --> 00:37:34.036
We haven't done that yet, but I think something certainly we can explore.

655
00:37:37.216 --> 00:37:41.196
So we've been fortunate through a new opportunity from NCI to build

656
00:37:41.716 --> 00:37:44.116
what was referred to as the next generation cohort.

657
00:37:45.036 --> 00:37:48.456
And this is a building phase of the cohort, and so we are recruiting

658
00:37:48.616 --> 00:37:51.276
20,000 Asian Americans nationally across the US.

659
00:37:52.076 --> 00:37:55.256
And with that, there's a big emphasis on community engagement.

660
00:37:55.556 --> 00:37:58.676
And also recognizing as this, we're using modern

661
00:37:58.716 --> 00:38:02.516
technologies similar to digital and online recruitment, but

662
00:38:02.656 --> 00:38:06.176
there is a really important emphasis in terms of working with our community

663
00:38:06.276 --> 00:38:09.016
partners. And so that element of building trust.

664
00:38:10.096 --> 00:38:13.476
We have five sites who have known relationships with

665
00:38:13.836 --> 00:38:17.776
specific Asian American community groups, and we know that we need to

666
00:38:17.836 --> 00:38:17.996
meet

667
00:38:18.836 --> 00:38:21.936
our community members with what they are most comfortable with in terms of

668
00:38:21.956 --> 00:38:25.776
participating. So for just an example, I think I saw

669
00:38:25.836 --> 00:38:27.336
Jane in the room from Cedars.

