00:38:39.236 --> 00:38:40.076
They'll hold

674
00:38:41.176 --> 00:38:44.676
informational session on cancer screening, which people are interested in.

675
00:38:45.036 --> 00:38:48.136
It builds trust and engagements with leaders in their

676
00:38:48.156 --> 00:38:50.796
community. And then we talk to them about Aspire.

677
00:38:51.316 --> 00:38:55.106
So, this is an effective approach, but of course, that takes time,

678
00:38:55.276 --> 00:38:58.806
right? Our primary method is digital and online because we really want to be able

679
00:38:58.806 --> 00:39:02.616
to be efficient, right, in terms of recruiting of individuals,

680
00:39:02.716 --> 00:39:06.326
processing. But we know that we need to be flexible and have different

681
00:39:06.356 --> 00:39:06.996
modalities

682
00:39:07.836 --> 00:39:11.616
to be able to reach all the community members to represent the Asian

683
00:39:11.656 --> 00:39:14.356
community. So that's one lesson that we've learned.

684
00:39:14.636 --> 00:39:18.416
Another lesson that we've learned is that I think all of us are faced with the

685
00:39:18.475 --> 00:39:21.256
challenges of acquiring identifiers, right?

686
00:39:21.516 --> 00:39:25.376
And we know that we need identifiers such as addresses and phone numbers because

687
00:39:25.436 --> 00:39:28.765
ultimately we need to do linkages, right? So how do we frame this question?

688
00:39:29.276 --> 00:39:33.126
Because we're all very protective, and we know the importance of having these

689
00:39:33.156 --> 00:39:36.526
down the road, right? And so that's one of the things that we're kind of grappling

690
00:39:36.556 --> 00:39:40.536
with in terms of really being able to get the kind of identifying information we

691
00:39:40.576 --> 00:39:40.816
need.

692
00:39:41.736 --> 00:39:45.596
And then I think the third thing I wanted to highlight, and I'm not sure how many

693
00:39:45.676 --> 00:39:49.456
others in the room have had experience with, was that our community advisory board

694
00:39:49.576 --> 00:39:52.265
was very clear that we need to offer incentives, right?

695
00:39:52.856 --> 00:39:56.816
And so with offering incentives, this was a whole other field that

696
00:39:56.936 --> 00:40:00.636
I didn't realize was occurring, and this actually was highlighted

697
00:40:00.896 --> 00:40:04.476
in a "Nature News" article, is that there are AI

698
00:40:04.536 --> 00:40:07.696
chatbots and things called click farms where there

