00:40:07.936 --> 00:40:08.716
are

700
00:40:09.916 --> 00:40:13.336
people pretending to be participants. So they're fraudulent actors, right?

701
00:40:13.876 --> 00:40:17.796
And so with that, you need to develop a system to

702
00:40:17.856 --> 00:40:21.686
address and identify them. And we've done a lot of

703
00:40:21.716 --> 00:40:25.026
work in trying to sort this out and in talking to other

704
00:40:25.836 --> 00:40:28.036
cohort leaders who are also developing cohort.

705
00:40:28.096 --> 00:40:31.076
I think this is a common problem, but we haven't collectively...

706
00:40:31.156 --> 00:40:34.886
I think that sharing of information, I think, to try to address this collectively

707
00:40:34.916 --> 00:40:38.466
as a field is really important. So just to highlight some of the measures that

708
00:40:38.476 --> 00:40:42.376
we've been using. So if we get an address, we geocode it, and then we

709
00:40:42.456 --> 00:40:46.236
categorize it. Is it really precise? Is it possibly fraudulent?

710
00:40:46.376 --> 00:40:48.996
Is it unlikely, or is it just missing?

711
00:40:49.856 --> 00:40:51.536
We look for pattern recognitions, right?

712
00:40:51.596 --> 00:40:53.816
So is there something funky in the email domains?

713
00:40:53.876 --> 00:40:55.656
Is there something strange in the patterns?

714
00:40:56.456 --> 00:41:00.296
Or their names, they report two first names or just something

715
00:41:00.436 --> 00:41:02.156
strange. So we go through that.

716
00:41:03.476 --> 00:41:06.416
We also look at positive aspects, right?

717
00:41:07.576 --> 00:41:11.436
We are offering ultimately our survey in seven,

718
00:41:11.816 --> 00:41:14.916
I think seven Asian languages. And so are they using a

719
00:41:14.936 --> 00:41:18.856
non-English survey? Do they report that they were recruited

