00:41:18.876 --> 00:41:20.726
by a community resource?

721
00:41:21.586 --> 00:41:24.186
Are their names consistent with their target ethnicity?

722
00:41:24.336 --> 00:41:28.196
So we have a whole host of measures to try to identify

723
00:41:28.256 --> 00:41:31.515
this, but this is definitely something that's happening across the field,

724
00:41:32.196 --> 00:41:36.016
that I think there needs to be a lot of additional conversations, and of

725
00:41:36.056 --> 00:41:37.636
course, this takes time and resources, right?

726
00:41:38.276 --> 00:41:40.236
We also have to make some phone calls.

727
00:41:40.316 --> 00:41:43.556
So these are a lot of some of the challenges that we're working through.

728
00:41:46.996 --> 00:41:48.536
Anyone else want to comment on that?

729
00:41:49.456 --> 00:41:52.156
Well, it's been interesting.

730
00:41:53.156 --> 00:41:54.596
I've been in the field maybe too long.

731
00:41:55.336 --> 00:41:57.416
Things have cycled back in our retention.

732
00:41:57.476 --> 00:41:59.246
We're back to using paper

733
00:42:00.676 --> 00:42:02.276
because we get better response rates.

734
00:42:03.876 --> 00:42:06.296
Well, you have to have multimodal, right?

